How can you insert an item into a binary search tree? ; I wrote my code but not sure about its correctness. Can anybody tell me whether it's correct?

TreeNode* BinarySearchTree::InsertTree(TreeNode* tnPtr,
                                                  const TreeItemType& item)

throw (TreeException)
{
     // Inserting an item
     if(tnPtr == NULL){
     tnPtr = new TreeNode(item);
     return tnPtr;
  }
     if(item == tnPtr->item_)
     return tnPtr;
     if(item <= tnPtr->item_){
     tnPtr->left_ =  InsertTree(tnPtr->left_, item);
     return tnPtr;
  }
     else if(item > tnPtr->item){
     tnPtr->right_ = InsertTree(tnPtr->right_, item);
     return tnPtr;
  }

} ; I looked through it pretty carefully, and I believe
it is correct.  I would, however, like to make a
couple of comments.

First, this code makes no attempt at balancing the
trees, so you can easily end up with a linked list
rather than a binary tree.  Consider if you created
the tree by passing in a set of sorted values.

Second, from the perspective of understanding the
flow, it's a little harder when a routine has so
many distinct return points.  I'm not sure if it is
better, but at least consider the following code
which is semantically identical:

TreeNode* InsertTree( TreeNode* tnPtr, const TreeItemType& item)
{
    // Inserting an item
    if(tnPtr == NULL)
        tnPtr = new TreeNode(item);

    if(item < tnPtr->item_)
        tnPtr->left_ = InsertTree(tnPtr->left_, item);
    else if(item > tnPtr->item_)
        tnPtr->right_ = InsertTree(tnPtr->right_, item);

    return tnPtr;
}

